      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's crazy that you mention the gutenberg bible. i was looking at a high-res scan of a 15th century folio and i swear the gaps between the capital letters aren't just random... they almost look like coordinates or some kind of topographical sequence. if we were to try and \"read\" the whitespace as data, what kind of logical framework should we use to interpret it? how do we actually translate the gaps into something readable?",
